'''{{mp|2013 RH|74}}''' is an [[Apollo asteroid]] and a [[near-Earth object]]<ref name="jpl-database">{{cite web |url=http://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=2013RH74;cad=1 |title=JPL Small-Body Database Browser: (2013 RH74) |publisher=[[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]] |access-date=4 April 2016}}</ref> discovered in September 2013 by the [[Catalina Sky Survey]]. The asteroid is roughly 300 meters in diameter. It was listed on the [[Sentry Risk Table]] in September 2013.<ref>http://neo.jpl.nasa.gov/risk/removed.html</ref> It was detected by [[radar astronomy|radar]] soon after discovery.<ref name=at5562>[http://www.astronomerstelegram.org/?read=5562 Broadband Photometry of the Potentially Hazardous Asteroid 2013 RH74]</ref> On 2013-Oct-17 the asteroid passed {{convert|0.05258|AU|km mi|abbr=on|lk=on}} from Earth.<ref name="jpl-database"/>

