{{Refimprove|date=February 2016}}
'''Si 363''' is a [[Silanes#Organosilanes|bifunctional organosilane]] [[chemical]] used in the reinforcement of [[rubber]] articles, especially [[tire]]s. SI363 is the trade name of a [[silane]] [[Chemical bond|bonding]] agent in the trialkoxymercaptoalkyl-silane class and of formula SH(CH<sub>2</sub>)H<sub>3</sub>Si(OCHH<sub>2</sub>CHH<sub>3</sub>)(O(CHH<sub>2</sub>CHH<sub>2</sub>O)H<sub>5</sub>(CHH<sub>2</sub>)H<sub>12</sub>CHH<sub>3</sub>)H<sub>2</sub>.<ref name=patent>{{cite web |url=http://www.google.com/patents/WO2014068486A1?cl=en |title=Tread compound production method - WO 2014068486 A1 |publisher=IFI CLAIMS Patent Services |access-date=20 February 2016}}</ref>

When applied to tires, Si 363 reduces [[rolling resistance]],<ref name=patent/> thus leading to increased [[Fuel economy in automobiles|fuel economy]]. Both [[alkoxsilicon]] and [[sulfur]] entities are present within its [[molecular structure]].

